verbose_text: Increase in occurrence of beta-catenin in nuclear, WIF1 cell versus vector cell) and cytoplasmic protein subfractions, as well as increase of c-myc in the WIF1 cells treated with LiCl, is consistent with observable increase in expression of nppb and actalpha1 mRNAs, while the occurrence of beta-catenin in nuclear and cytoplasmic protein subfractions were further inhibited as well as decreased of c-myc in the WIF1 cells treated with Fz-8/Fc, in consistent with observable decrease in the expression of nppb and actalpha1 mRNAs.
evidence: expression of nppb                                                         and actalpha1                                                         mRNAs
